The paper discusses attack analysis results for the DARPA Transparent Computing Program, which involves developing secure computing systems. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The analysis was performed using machine learning techniques, which suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The program also involves developing software and hardware systems, which could fall under software engineering (cs.SE) and distributed computing (cs.DC). Finally, the program aims to increase transparency and accountability in computing systems, which could fall under social and information networks (cs.SI).
